<p>(serves one).</p>
<ol>
<li>Go out and buy a little <strong>rosemary</strong> plant. Plant it in your garden. </li>
<li>Pull off a sprig. Take it inside.</li>
<li>Take one frozen <strong>chicken breast</strong>, and cut it up into thin slices. Marinade with rosemary and crushed red and black pepper.</li>
<li>Go watch some TV</li>
<li>On medium-high heat, fry the chicken with a dab of olive oil.</li>
<li>While the chicken is cooking, cut up one<strong>green bell pepper</strong> and one <strong>small onion</strong></li>
<li>When the chicken is almost done cooking, throw in the veggies.</li>
<li>Stir it all around for a minute or so.</li>
<li>Pour in a large splash of <strong>merlot</strong></li>
<li>Stir it all around for a minute or so.</li>
<li>Add a cover and steam for a minute or so.</li>
<li>Stir fry until the juice is almost gone, then serve.</li>
</ol>

